tive health and will be greatly appreciated by linguists, historians, and students of Hawaiian language and culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aMEDICAL / Anatomy.2bisacsh1 aBushnell, O. A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMookini, Esther T.1 aMookini, Esther T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoung, Benjamin B. C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUHP eBook Package 2000-2013z978311056414308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066325940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082484500140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824845001423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824845001.jpg  a978-3-11-056414-3  UHP eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066325-9  University of Hawaii Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK